Description: Limestone ostracon: on recto and verso respectively eighteen and sixteen lines of a continuous text recording a list of victuals given by a lady Tadjepehu to a lady Henutshe in certain months.
Curator's comments: Formerly 5639a; = J. J. Černy and A.H. Gardiner, ‘Hieratic Ostraca’ (Oxford 1957), pl. 85.a Bibliography: S. Birch, 'Inscriptions in the Hieratic and Demotic Character, from the Collections of the British Museum' (London, 1868), pl.XXVIII; A. Erman, 'Zeitschrift für Ägyptische Sprache und Altertumskunde' 39 (1902), pp.128ff R. van Walsem, 'Month-names and Feasts at Deir el-Medina', in R.J Demaree and J.J. Janssen (eds), 'Gleanings from Deir el-Medîna' (Leiden, 1982), pp.215ff.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136370) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136370)
